content.text:
Let me analyze the target image and provide instructions for building both structures.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
The image shows two separate structures:

Left Structure:
- A house-like structure on stilts
- 4 layers including roof
- Uses blue, red, green, yellow, and orange blocks
- Has a triangular orange roof

Right Structure:
- A tower-like structure on orange cylinders
- 4 layers including roof
- Uses blue, red, green, and orange blocks
- Has a triangular orange roof
- Sits on two orange cylindrical logs

Let me provide the assembly instructions for both structures:

Left Structure:
{
Step1: Move block with index 1 (blue cube - left leg)
Step2: Move block with index 1 (blue cube - right leg)
Step3: Move block with index 10 (yellow horizontal block as platform)
Step4: Move block with index 1 (blue cube - left wall)
Step5: Move block with index 3 (red cube - right wall)
Step6: Move block with index 7 (green horizontal block)
Step7: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular roof)
}

Right Structure:
{
Step1: Move block with index 11 (orange cylinder)
Step2: Move block with index 11 (orange cylinder)
Step3: Move block with index 7 (green horizontal block as base)
Step4: Move block with index 1 (blue cube - bottom)
Step5: Move block with index 3 (red cube - middle)
Step6: Move block with index 1 (blue cube - top)
Step7: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular roof)
}

The blocks must be placed exactly as shown in the dictionary image, without any rotation. Each step builds upon the previous ones to create the final structures.
